<HEADLINE>
PANAMA EXPRESSES THANKS FOR TAIWAN DONATION
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Panama City, March 9 (CNA) 03/09/07  21:08:57 (By Ramon Huang and
Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Panamanian First Vice President and Foreign Affairs Minister
Samuel Lewis has expressed gratitude at a donation ceremony
Thursday on behalf of the Panamanian government and President
Martin Torrijos for Taiwan's financial help and promised to
strengthen bilateral relations, Republic of China Ambassador Ho
Ping-fu said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ho said at the donation ceremony at Panama's Ministry of Foreign
Affairs that Taiwan's donation to Panama, a part of this year's
bilateral cooperation project, will help Panama build bamboo
houses for its indigenous people, construct underground water
systems, renovate a sports center and establish a soccer stadium.
</P>
<P>
According to Ho, Taiwan will build 300 bamboo houses urgently
needed by Panamanian aborigines in remote districts in order to
improve their standard of living.
</P>
<P>
The underground water system between the country's capital,
Panama City, and its second-largest city, Colon, will provide
clean drinking water.
</P>
<P>
Lewis said at the ceremony that Panama and Taiwan are involved in
various government-to-government cooperation projects and that
all of Taiwan's donation money is managed with transparency under
government supervision.
</P>
